Either "SED"   (sedentary) number weeks training ("1W", "2W", "4W", "8W"). total_ketones numeric; total ketone bodies (\(\mu\)mol/L). nefa numeric; non-esterified fatty acids (NEFA). lactate numeric; lactate (mmol/L). glucose numeric; glucose (mg/dL). glycerol numeric; glycerol (mg/dL). glucagon numeric; glucagon (pmol). insulin numeric; insulin (pg/mL). insulin_iu numeric; insulin (\(\mu\)IU/mL) using   conversion 1 pg/mL = 0.023 \(\mu\)IU/mL provided package insert. leptin numeric; leptin (pg/mL). corticosterone numeric; corticosterone (ng/mL). ins_gcg_ratio numeric; molar insulin/glucagon ratio.   Calculated (insulin (pg/mL) / 5.804 (Da)) / glucagon (pmol). homa_ir numeric; Homeostatic Model Assessment Insulin   Resistance (HOMA-IR). Insulin (\(\mu\)IU/mL) x glucose (mg/dL)   / 405.

title: Differential analysis results — WATSC_DA
text: named list 3 data.frame objects:  "trained_vs_SED" trained timepoints compared     sex-matched sedentary control group. Example: F_1W - F_SED. Total 8     contrasts. "MvF_SED" Sedentary males compared sedentary females. 1     contrast. "MvF_exercise_response" Comparisons male female     training responses. Example: (M_8W - M_SED) - (F_8W - F_SED). Total 4     contrasts. addition columns present MSnbase::fData tables,   data.frame contains following 8 variables:  logFC numeric; difference weighted mean log\(_2\)     values groups specified contrast column. AveExpr numeric; mean log\(_2\) relative abundance     feature. t numeric; LIMMA moderated t-statistic. P.Value numeric; p-value. adj.P.Val numeric; Benjamini-Hochberg adjusted p-value.     P-values adjusted across contrasts. feature character; uniquely defines feature     tested. feature_ID. contrast factor; contrast(s) tested. se numeric; standard error (SE)     logFC column.
